      "span_text": "Colin Havenar-Daughton (La Jolla Institute of Allergy and Immunology) and Matthias Pauthner (TSRI) presented results from a large Scripps CHAVI-ID rhesus macaque study showing that subcutaneous immunization of rhesus macaques at 0, 8, and 24 weeks with BG505 SOSIP consistently elicited higher titers of autologous neutralizing antibodies when compared with intramuscular immunization or immunizations with a shorter interval between the prime and first booster."
